# Rani Beauty Clinic — Cursor Rules

## Project
Luxury medical aesthetics clinic website + AI-powered operations dashboard.
Live at ranibeautyclinic.com (Vercel). Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS.

## Critical Rules
- Rani does IM INJECTIONS only. NEVER use the word "infusion." Always say "injection."
- Brand voice: luxury, confident, clinically-assured. Educational + aspirational. Never discount-first. "Transformation journey" not "treatment list."
- Use `@/*` path alias (maps to `./src/*`)
- All data fetching goes through Airtable (`src/lib/airtable/`) — never direct DB calls
- Dashboard API routes live in `src/app/api/dashboard/`
- Auth uses JWT via jose (HS256), cookie-based sessions (`src/lib/auth/`)
- Rate limit Airtable to 4.7 req/sec (use `src/lib/cache/` for TTL caching)

## Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14.2 (App Router)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS with custom theme (rani-navy #0F1D2C, rani-gold #F3D6BE, rani-cream #FAF8F5)
- Fonts: Playfair Display (headings), Montserrat (body)
- Animation: Framer Motion
- Charts: Recharts
- Icons: Lucide React
- State: SWR for data fetching (25 hooks in `src/hooks/useDashboardData.ts`)
- AI: Anthropic Claude API (`@anthropic-ai/sdk`)

## Architecture
- `src/app/` — Pages and API routes (App Router)
- `src/app/(dashboard)/` — Protected dashboard (RBAC, 5 roles)
- `src/app/api/dashboard/` — 58 dashboard API endpoints
- `src/components/` — React components (dashboard/, layout/, sections/, services/, ui/)
- `src/lib/` — Intelligence engines and integrations
- `src/data/` — Static data (services, blog, locations)
- `src/hooks/` — SWR data hooks
- `src/types/` — TypeScript interfaces

## Intelligence Engines (src/lib/)
- Churn prediction, no-show prediction, revenue anomaly detection
- Treatment recommendations, dynamic pricing, P&L intelligence
- Schedule optimizer, inventory auto-manager
- AI consult co-pilot, RAG knowledge base

## Integrations
- Booking: Mangomint (CompanyID: 876418)
- Payments: Square (POS), Stripe (checkout)
- Email: Resend | SMS: Twilio | Voice: Vapi.ai
- Database: Airtable (12 tables)
- Vector DB: Pinecone (RAG)

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional components only
- Server components by default, 'use client' only when needed
- Prefer named exports
- Use Tailwind utilities, avoid inline styles
- Error boundaries for dashboard sections
